WEBVTT

00:05.135 --> 00:06.180
Son of a bitch!

00:06.223 --> 00:08.051
[ Grunts ]

00:08.095 --> 00:12.055
[ Crying ]

00:12.099 --> 00:13.100
Someone
was looking for me.

00:13.143 --> 00:15.102
Someone like
Ronald Pergman?

00:15.145 --> 00:17.669
That RV -- it's been
sitting there for a while.

00:17.713 --> 00:19.671
Registered to a guy, reported
stolen from a gas station.

00:19.715 --> 00:21.282
Let's pull the gas station
surveillance video.

00:21.325 --> 00:22.935
What do you want me
to do with this guy?

00:22.979 --> 00:24.285
Dietrich: Kill him.

00:24.328 --> 00:26.374
Is there
a dead man in there?
Nope.

00:27.331 --> 00:29.246
You're a traitor. Huh?

00:29.290 --> 00:31.161
It's not what you think, man!
It's not what you think!

00:31.205 --> 00:33.250
We need your help.We did something wrong.

00:33.294 --> 00:35.774
"I would like my money, pretty
please, with sugar on top."

00:35.818 --> 00:37.298
I don't have your money.

00:37.341 --> 00:38.299
You got 24 hours.

00:38.342 --> 00:39.909
We're looking for
Bridger Ryan.

00:39.952 --> 00:40.953
Sensei Gary:
I don't know who that is.

00:40.997 --> 00:42.433
[ Groans ]

00:42.477 --> 00:44.435
-I messed up so bad.
-We'll take care of this.

00:44.479 --> 00:46.176
I hope you're gonna do
what we discussed.

00:46.220 --> 00:47.351
I don't know
the correct dose.

00:47.395 --> 00:48.787
A killing dose.

00:48.831 --> 00:50.920
You are an unfit mother!

00:50.963 --> 00:53.314
Aah! No!

00:53.357 --> 00:54.750
[ Both grunting ]

00:56.752 --> 00:57.883
We're getting
out of here.

00:57.927 --> 00:59.320
[ Grunts ]

00:59.363 --> 01:01.539
-[ Screams ]
-[ Groans ]

01:01.583 --> 01:03.150
[ Grunts ]

01:03.193 --> 01:04.151
[ Groans ]

01:17.599 --> 01:23.605
♪♪

01:23.648 --> 01:29.915
♪♪

01:29.959 --> 01:36.139
♪♪

01:36.183 --> 01:42.189
♪♪

01:42.232 --> 01:48.543
♪♪

01:48.586 --> 01:50.414
[ Seatbelt rattles ]

01:57.421 --> 01:59.206
Okay.

02:00.120 --> 02:02.644
Be right back in two shakes
of a lamb's tail.

02:02.687 --> 02:05.386
Don't leave me with him.

02:05.429 --> 02:06.343
It's okay.
I'll protect you.

02:07.562 --> 02:08.432
Ew.

02:10.086 --> 02:11.566
[ Scarlet sighs ]

02:11.609 --> 02:13.568
Phoebe...

02:13.611 --> 02:16.223
We're going to Alaska
when this is all over.

02:16.266 --> 02:18.225
What if I don't want to
go to Alaska?

02:18.268 --> 02:21.315
Then you'll miss out
on all the fun.

02:21.358 --> 02:23.230
We're going to live
in a cabin.

02:23.273 --> 02:25.841
Going to be paradise.

02:25.884 --> 02:27.843
That doesn't sound
like paradise.

02:27.886 --> 02:30.411
Arthur has a plan
for us.

02:30.454 --> 02:32.978
Okay? We just need to
make sure he gets better.

02:33.022 --> 02:35.459
Stop calling him that.

02:35.503 --> 02:37.635
I know his name --

02:37.679 --> 02:39.289
his real name.

02:41.248 --> 02:44.425
I'm sorry
that I lied to you.

02:44.468 --> 02:47.254
It won't happen again.
I promise.

02:48.646 --> 02:51.345
Honey, I know.
[ Sniffles ]

02:51.388 --> 02:53.216
Why don't you watch
one of your videos?

02:53.260 --> 02:55.697
That's a good idea.

02:55.740 --> 03:01.006
And...I will be...

03:01.050 --> 03:02.312
right back.

03:12.757 --> 03:15.456
Do you wanna sing
a song?

03:15.499 --> 03:17.414
No.

03:17.458 --> 03:18.981
Why would I want to sing
a song?

03:21.679 --> 03:25.901
♪ The wheels on the bus
go round and round ♪

03:25.944 --> 03:27.119
♪ Round and round

03:27.163 --> 03:28.643
I don't think
that would work.

03:28.686 --> 03:31.298
Well, I'm gonna protect you
and your mother, Phoebe.

03:31.341 --> 03:32.908
I don't think so.

03:32.951 --> 03:37.869
♪♪

03:37.913 --> 03:40.045
You're going to die.

03:40.089 --> 03:42.439
I had a dream about it.

03:42.483 --> 03:44.354
None of my dreams
ever came true.

03:47.357 --> 03:50.186
My mother always said it's a sin
to talk about your dreams.

03:52.493 --> 03:54.364
She called them
"dirty movies."

03:54.408 --> 03:59.891
♪♪

04:06.246 --> 04:08.726
[ Dog whining ]

04:12.034 --> 04:14.689
[ Gasping, coughing ]

04:14.732 --> 04:16.386
[ Groans ]

04:16.430 --> 04:21.217
♪♪

04:21.261 --> 04:26.309
♪♪

04:26.353 --> 04:28.180
Tubb: Rising body count
and no one behind bars.

04:28.224 --> 04:29.704
You can imagine the kind of
political pressure I'm under.

04:29.747 --> 04:31.358
These kids are
at the center of everything.

04:31.401 --> 04:33.925
Their testimony
gets me close to an arrest.

04:33.969 --> 04:35.797
Bridger Ryan
was a student here.

04:35.840 --> 04:37.712
He was with Gary Klevorn
at the time of the murder.

04:37.755 --> 04:39.235
And Bridger gave
the initial description

04:39.279 --> 04:40.671
that matches
Ren Bhullar's brother, Jag.

04:40.715 --> 04:42.107
Oh, well,
that's just great.

04:42.151 --> 04:43.718
Now we got two Bhullars
in town.

04:43.761 --> 04:45.415
Why haven't you
brought him in?

04:45.459 --> 04:46.677
We need to
get eyes on him.

04:46.721 --> 04:48.418
You, wait? Since when?

04:48.462 --> 04:50.594
Ha ha.

04:50.638 --> 04:52.683
So the cartel did come looking
for their drugs and money.

04:52.727 --> 04:54.772
If we want these bodies
to stop dropping,

04:54.816 --> 04:56.426
I think this T-Lock
is the key.

04:57.862 --> 05:00.256
Let's hope you're right.

05:02.389 --> 05:04.739
Jenny: Thanks for sitting down
with us again.

05:04.782 --> 05:06.523
Max is just trying to do
the right thing.

05:06.567 --> 05:08.003
And what about you?

05:08.046 --> 05:10.048
You told me T-Lock
found the drugs.

05:10.092 --> 05:11.267
That was a lie.

05:11.311 --> 05:13.356
I was protecting
my daughter.

05:13.400 --> 05:15.097
Or maybe you were trying
to cover for your boyfriend.

05:17.404 --> 05:18.796
When was the last time
you talked to him?

05:18.840 --> 05:20.276
Has he reached out to you?

05:20.320 --> 05:22.583
No. I --My mom's telling
the truth.

05:22.626 --> 05:26.369
Look, Max, I know you mean well,
but you don't understand

05:26.413 --> 05:28.328
how many people got hurt
'cause of your actions.

05:30.417 --> 05:32.114
I do.

05:32.854 --> 05:34.638
I know.

05:36.901 --> 05:39.556
[ Voice breaking ]
I know, and I'm sorry.

05:39.600 --> 05:40.601
[ Sniffles ]

05:43.473 --> 05:46.128
I wish I could just take it back
and do it over again.

05:48.652 --> 05:51.394
T-Lock taking that money
is a serious problem,

05:51.438 --> 05:53.396
and the cartel is not gonna stop
until they find him.

05:54.658 --> 05:57.618
Did they shoot
Bridger's karate instructor?

05:57.661 --> 05:59.620
These are not the sort of people
you want to mess with.

06:05.016 --> 06:06.453
Hey.

06:06.496 --> 06:08.629
Hey, don't worry.

06:08.672 --> 06:11.371
I'm gonna do everything I can
to try to keep you safe.

06:14.286 --> 06:15.592
[ Telephones ringing ]

06:15.636 --> 06:17.289
What do you think?

06:17.333 --> 06:19.466
I think they're scared,
as they should be.

06:19.509 --> 06:21.511
Let's get a unit on them,
24/7.

06:21.555 --> 06:23.252
I already looked
into it.

06:23.295 --> 06:24.427
Tubb says we don't have
the resources --

06:24.471 --> 06:25.994
scraping butter
on too much bread.

06:26.037 --> 06:27.212
Are those his words
or yours?

06:27.256 --> 06:28.562
I added the last part.

06:28.605 --> 06:30.302
"Scraping butter
on too much bread" --

06:30.346 --> 06:32.217
that sounds pretty good.

06:32.261 --> 06:34.611
Okay, well, let's get
a drive-by going, at least.

06:34.655 --> 06:36.134
Hey, what's the holdup
on that stolen RV?

06:36.178 --> 06:37.614
The surveillance footage.

06:37.658 --> 06:39.268
I'm pushing, but they've got
this whole protocol --

06:39.311 --> 06:40.922
Well, just keep pushing.
Cassie deserves answers.

06:40.965 --> 06:42.663
Hoyt, just because
someone stole an RV

06:42.706 --> 06:44.447
doesn't mean
they killed somebody.Doesn't mean they didn't.

06:44.491 --> 06:46.449
Just chase them down.[ Telephone rings ]

06:46.493 --> 06:48.451
Hoyt -- Dispatch.

06:48.495 --> 06:50.018
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

06:50.061 --> 06:52.194
This is Deputy Poppernak.

06:53.282 --> 06:54.457
We're on it.

06:54.501 --> 06:55.589
[ Cellphone beeps ]

06:55.632 --> 06:56.633
What's up?

06:56.677 --> 06:58.592
Jag Bhullar.

07:00.855 --> 07:02.683
Lock it in.

07:02.726 --> 07:06.730
♪♪

07:10.081 --> 07:12.519
Okay. Let's say you were right
and Ronald killed my father.

07:12.562 --> 07:15.043
Whoa. That's not exactly
what I said.

07:15.086 --> 07:17.480
You implied it.Okay, but, to be clear,

07:17.524 --> 07:19.482
I-I told you
I can't shake the feeling

07:19.526 --> 07:22.050
that Wolf Legarski
is connected to Ronald somehow.

07:22.093 --> 07:24.052
[ Sighs ] That's it?

07:24.095 --> 07:25.488
What I mean is,
maybe he really knows

07:25.532 --> 07:27.838
where Ronald is
or is helping him.

07:27.882 --> 07:29.361
What about
the cereal thing?

07:29.405 --> 07:31.276
Well, yeah, okay,
there's that, too,

07:31.320 --> 07:33.714
but none of it matters.

07:33.757 --> 07:37.326
Even if Wolf is helping Ronald
or working with him,

07:37.369 --> 07:39.197
why would Ronald risk so much
to kill your father?

07:40.242 --> 07:42.070
Wolf's ranch. Where is it?

07:42.113 --> 07:43.941
Cassie, there's no way
I'm letting you go there alone.

07:43.985 --> 07:46.509
Okay.
Then we go together.

07:48.772 --> 07:50.513
[ Grunts ]

07:50.557 --> 07:52.167
[ Groans ]

07:52.210 --> 07:55.475
[ Breathing heavily ]

07:57.564 --> 08:02.786
♪♪

08:02.830 --> 08:05.006
[ Groans ]

08:05.049 --> 08:14.668
♪♪

08:14.711 --> 08:17.366
[ Grunts, breathing heavily ]

08:17.409 --> 08:25.635
♪♪

08:25.679 --> 08:27.202
[ Gasps ]

08:27.245 --> 08:29.552
[ Groaning ]

08:29.596 --> 08:37.038
♪♪

08:37.081 --> 08:39.127
[ Panting ]

08:39.170 --> 08:46.047
♪♪

08:46.090 --> 08:48.179
[ Inhales sharply, groans ]

08:49.616 --> 08:51.618
[ Crow caws ]

08:51.661 --> 08:55.491
[ Door creaks ]

08:55.535 --> 08:59.190
♪♪

08:59.234 --> 09:01.062
Have a good night's
sleep?

09:01.105 --> 09:02.977
Bob here
is feeling generous.

09:03.020 --> 09:05.457
He, uh, brought you
a last meal.

09:05.501 --> 09:06.981
Let me out of here.

09:07.024 --> 09:08.548
You're never
getting out.

09:09.853 --> 09:11.463
I-I can get you
your money back.

09:11.507 --> 09:12.639
D, I can help you.

09:12.682 --> 09:14.597
Shoot him in the gut.

09:14.641 --> 09:16.077
Let him bleed out.

09:16.120 --> 09:18.601
My pleasure.Listen, I --

09:18.645 --> 09:21.648
I-I can help you restart
your entire operation, D.

09:21.691 --> 09:23.084
Do it.Whoa, okay.

09:23.127 --> 09:24.607
Dietrich,
you got this all wrong.

09:24.651 --> 09:25.869
I'm a cop.

09:25.913 --> 09:27.610
D!

09:27.654 --> 09:29.656
Okay? I'm a cop.

09:29.699 --> 09:33.137
♪♪

09:38.229 --> 09:40.623
[ Laughs ]
Well, he's lying.

09:40.667 --> 09:42.016
I'm not -- I'm not after you,
okay?

09:42.059 --> 09:43.452
I'm after the Bhullars.

09:43.495 --> 09:45.236
Come on. Let's kill
this soft son of a bitch.

09:45.280 --> 09:46.673
They're -- They're gonna
wipe you out.

09:46.716 --> 09:49.066
And maybe I can help you
get them first, hmm?

09:49.110 --> 09:50.198
We don't need
your help.

09:50.241 --> 09:51.678
You could be
the only game in town!

09:51.721 --> 09:55.072
'Cause you said it yourself!

09:55.116 --> 09:57.553
Come on!
I'm the only shot that you got.

09:57.597 --> 10:05.169
♪♪

10:06.344 --> 10:10.827
Ugh.
So much natural light.

10:10.871 --> 10:13.830
Tonya, I love it.

10:13.874 --> 10:16.572
Luckily, the guy
who was gonna buy it died.

10:16.616 --> 10:19.140
Donno.

10:19.183 --> 10:20.837
Have some respect
for the dead.

10:20.881 --> 10:22.665
Sorry.

10:22.709 --> 10:25.712
Tonya, ever heard
of 4-ANPP?

10:25.755 --> 10:27.104
No.

10:27.148 --> 10:29.498
My family imports it in bulk
from Delhi.

10:29.541 --> 10:32.675
They truck it to a plant
in Brampton,

10:32.719 --> 10:36.331
and -- poof -- out comes
40 kilos of synthetic fentanyl.

10:36.374 --> 10:38.855
Only problem is
that we've had some trouble

10:38.899 --> 10:40.161
getting it
into the States.

10:40.204 --> 10:41.728
Here?

10:42.859 --> 10:45.470
You wanna manufacture
here?

10:45.514 --> 10:47.864
Local hub for the entire
Mountain West.

10:47.908 --> 10:49.866
I even hired a chemist.

10:49.910 --> 10:51.476
Med student,
good Indian family,

10:51.520 --> 10:54.915
living out his parents' dreams
at U of M.

10:54.958 --> 10:56.220
We just got to figure out
shipping.

10:57.439 --> 11:00.181
I need safe and secure
transport.

11:00.224 --> 11:02.357
I think I might know
some people.

11:04.751 --> 11:07.188
What would we do
without Tonya, hmm?
Mm.

11:07.231 --> 11:09.277
Let me see what I can do.

11:09.320 --> 11:10.800
[ Door opens ]

11:14.891 --> 11:16.197
[ Sighs ]

11:16.240 --> 11:17.720
Where's she headed off to?

11:17.764 --> 11:19.722
None of your beeswax.

11:19.766 --> 11:20.984
[ Door closes ]

11:21.028 --> 11:23.552
Dhruv, Donno,
give us the room.

11:23.595 --> 11:31.734
♪♪

11:31.778 --> 11:33.388
I already told you,

11:33.431 --> 11:34.998
we are not
setting up shop here.

11:35.042 --> 11:36.391
It's a bad idea.

11:36.434 --> 11:38.523
Okay.
Well, why don't I call Dad,

11:38.567 --> 11:40.874
walk him through the numbers,
see what he thinks?

11:40.917 --> 11:42.310
Wouldn't do that.

11:42.353 --> 11:45.008
Why? You afraid
it's a good idea?

11:45.052 --> 11:46.575
You need to learn
to stay in your lane.

11:46.618 --> 11:48.316
I don't work for you.
I work for Dad. Same as you.

11:48.359 --> 11:49.796
So don't talk to me
about lanes.

11:49.839 --> 11:51.667
No, it's not the same.

11:51.711 --> 11:52.842
Know your place.

11:53.800 --> 11:55.236
[ Knock on door ]

11:55.279 --> 11:56.628
Jenny:
Helena Sheriff's Department!

11:56.672 --> 11:57.934
Easy, boys.

12:03.157 --> 12:05.637
Told you
I'd see you again.

12:05.681 --> 12:08.379
I'm here for...
these two.

12:08.423 --> 12:10.860
We're gonna have a little chat
down at the station.

12:12.819 --> 12:13.820
Let's go.

12:20.043 --> 12:21.392
Aah!

12:22.176 --> 12:23.568
Were you careful?

12:23.612 --> 12:26.267
Yes. Always.

12:26.310 --> 12:28.617
[ Groaning ]

12:33.056 --> 12:35.189
Let me see.

12:42.413 --> 12:44.067
It's bad, isn't it?

12:46.026 --> 12:48.071
I'm gonna make it better.

12:48.115 --> 12:49.072
I promise.

12:52.075 --> 12:53.773
Then we leave for Alaska?

12:58.865 --> 13:00.954
You want that, don't you?

13:00.997 --> 13:04.218
Us, together as a family.

13:05.523 --> 13:08.309
Our little home
at the end of the world.

13:08.352 --> 13:10.659
Safe and happy.

13:10.702 --> 13:12.356
I do.

13:16.534 --> 13:18.623
I'm gonna go
get some supplies.

13:18.667 --> 13:20.887
Okay.

13:25.239 --> 13:27.894
Phoebe, come on.

13:27.937 --> 13:33.769
♪♪

13:33.813 --> 13:42.691
♪♪

13:42.734 --> 13:46.434
[ Indistinct conversations,
light music playing ]

13:46.477 --> 13:47.914
Woman over intercom:
Manager to aisle 3.

13:47.957 --> 13:49.741
Manager to aisle 3.

13:49.785 --> 13:57.706
♪♪

13:57.749 --> 14:05.932
♪♪

14:05.975 --> 14:07.759
Pharmacy, pick up 2.

14:07.803 --> 14:09.457
Pharmacy, pick up line 2.

14:09.500 --> 14:13.983
♪♪

14:14.027 --> 14:15.680
Why are you helping Ronald?

14:15.724 --> 14:17.900
Because we're a family.

14:17.944 --> 14:20.120
[ Gasps ]
Ooh, look what I found.

14:20.163 --> 14:21.904
New red barrettes.

14:21.948 --> 14:23.297
I don't want
a red barrette.

14:23.340 --> 14:25.038
I wanna go home!
[ Sighs ]

14:25.081 --> 14:27.692
Well, that's exactly
what we're doing, Phoebe.

14:27.736 --> 14:30.957
We're helping Ronald so we can
all go home, right?

14:31.000 --> 14:32.523
[ Sighs ]

14:32.567 --> 14:38.529
♪♪

14:38.573 --> 14:41.750
Wait, miss, I need to see
what's in your bag.

14:41.793 --> 14:42.751
Is there something wrong?

14:42.794 --> 14:44.100
Bag, please.

14:44.144 --> 14:46.102
-Mom.
-It's okay, honey.

14:46.146 --> 14:47.974
I'm just talking
to this nice man.

14:48.017 --> 14:49.758
I need to see
what's in that bag.

14:49.801 --> 14:51.934
Sure. Yeah.

14:51.978 --> 14:53.153
Andy.

14:53.196 --> 14:55.416
Andy -- that's a...

14:55.459 --> 14:58.941
strong name
for a strong man.

15:02.423 --> 15:03.859
[ Sighs ]

15:03.903 --> 15:05.513
Okay.

15:05.556 --> 15:13.173
♪♪

15:13.216 --> 15:15.958
If you don't let me go,
I'm gonna scream

15:16.002 --> 15:19.222
or stab you in the balls.
I haven't really decided yet.

15:19.266 --> 15:21.050
You're crazy.

15:21.094 --> 15:25.011
But I really, really need
those things, Andy.

15:25.054 --> 15:27.448
Okay?

15:27.491 --> 15:29.015
Now be a good boy.

15:29.058 --> 15:30.799
My mistake.

15:32.801 --> 15:34.759
Have a nice day, ma'am.Mm.

15:34.803 --> 15:36.805
Thank you.
Come on, Phoebe.

15:36.848 --> 15:38.589
Phoebe.
Come on, honey.

15:38.633 --> 15:40.591
Come on.

15:45.205 --> 15:47.772
This has been fun and all,

15:47.816 --> 15:49.078
but you don't have anything
that could keep me here.

15:49.122 --> 15:50.601
In fact,
I'm doing you a favor.

15:50.645 --> 15:52.386
I can walk my handsome self
out of here whenever I want.

15:52.429 --> 15:54.170
The only place you're going to
is prison.

15:54.214 --> 15:56.346
It's just a matter
of how long.

15:56.390 --> 15:59.045
You cooperate,
answer a few questions,

15:59.088 --> 16:02.135
maybe we can knock off
a decade, even two.

16:04.050 --> 16:08.010
[ Laughs ]

16:08.054 --> 16:09.316
Ah. Ah.

16:12.406 --> 16:13.711
Lawyer.

16:17.063 --> 16:19.021
We have a witness
that puts you at the dojo.

16:20.153 --> 16:21.676
Lawyer.

16:21.719 --> 16:23.417
How does it work?

16:23.460 --> 16:25.288
Do you take orders
from your father?

16:29.075 --> 16:31.903
L-A-W-Y-E-R.

16:33.166 --> 16:35.864
Or does your sister
tell you what to do?

16:35.907 --> 16:37.170
Do you kill for her, Jag?

16:37.213 --> 16:40.434
Are you her little
B-I-T-C-H?

16:44.090 --> 16:45.830
Lawyer, please.

16:45.874 --> 16:53.099
♪♪

16:53.142 --> 17:00.193
♪♪

17:00.236 --> 17:02.238
He didn't
give you much.

17:02.282 --> 17:04.458
Nothing except
that cocky smile.

17:04.501 --> 17:07.330
He does have great hair.

17:07.374 --> 17:08.984
Uh, what are you talking about?Profiling.

17:09.028 --> 17:11.247
Men with great hair have
an overabundance of confidence,

17:11.291 --> 17:12.727
which can be used
against them.

17:12.770 --> 17:15.338
Also, his posture...
I don't like it.

17:17.601 --> 17:19.473
Let's go check on
our witness.
Yeah.

17:19.516 --> 17:22.171
[ Door opens ]

17:22.215 --> 17:23.999
I need you to
find me drivers

17:24.043 --> 17:25.957
who can ship
across state lines.

17:26.001 --> 17:27.698
What's the cargo?

17:27.742 --> 17:30.527
Remember what I said
about no questions?

17:30.571 --> 17:32.007
If I don't know
what's in the box,

17:32.051 --> 17:33.661
then I ain't drivin' it.

17:33.704 --> 17:35.271
You just find me
the drivers,

17:35.315 --> 17:37.273
and I'll get you
some answers.

17:37.317 --> 17:39.493
It don't work
like that, Ton.

17:39.536 --> 17:41.930
[ Scoffs ]

17:41.973 --> 17:45.020
Well, Bryce,
the people I work for

17:45.064 --> 17:47.762
don't like questions.

17:47.805 --> 17:50.156
Matter of fact, they chop
people up who ask questions.

17:50.199 --> 17:53.115
Uh, okay.

17:53.159 --> 17:54.290
No. No, no, no,
no, no.

17:54.334 --> 17:56.205
I'm out, then.
No, you're not.

17:57.293 --> 17:59.121
You'll be
well compensated.

17:59.165 --> 18:02.298
Drive your truck.
Shut your mouth.

18:02.342 --> 18:03.908
Be on time.

18:03.952 --> 18:06.128
[ Scoffs ]

18:06.172 --> 18:08.304
Now, do we have a deal?

18:08.348 --> 18:11.133
Sounds like
I ain't got a choice.

18:11.177 --> 18:13.135
You're right.

18:13.179 --> 18:14.093
You don't.

18:16.834 --> 18:18.314
[ Car door opens ]

18:18.358 --> 18:20.621
I'll be in touch.

18:20.664 --> 18:25.843
♪♪

18:25.887 --> 18:27.236
[ Knock on door ]

18:27.280 --> 18:29.151
Housekeeping.

18:37.246 --> 18:48.083
♪♪

18:48.127 --> 18:49.215
Housekeeper:
Are you okay?

18:49.258 --> 18:50.216
Go away.

18:50.259 --> 18:52.653
I can call an ambulance.

18:54.655 --> 18:56.396
[ Gasps ]

18:56.439 --> 18:58.833
Aah!

18:58.876 --> 19:00.748
[ Choking ]

19:00.791 --> 19:03.403
[ Grunts ]

19:03.446 --> 19:05.100
Aah! Help!

19:05.144 --> 19:10.192
♪♪

19:10.236 --> 19:12.629
♪♪

19:12.673 --> 19:14.979
Wolf: Aggie?

19:15.023 --> 19:17.417
[ Breathing heavily ]

19:17.460 --> 19:20.289
Oh.

19:20.333 --> 19:28.210
♪♪

19:28.254 --> 19:32.127
[ Crying ]

19:32.171 --> 19:37.654
♪♪

19:37.698 --> 19:43.269
♪♪

19:49.666 --> 19:52.365
How are you, Bridger?
Holding up okay?

19:52.408 --> 19:53.409
Yeah.

19:55.977 --> 19:58.284
And your sister?

19:58.327 --> 20:00.242
Yeah, she's fine.

20:03.158 --> 20:06.161
We brought in the men who killed
your karate instructor.

20:06.205 --> 20:08.381
We just need you to confirm
their identity.

20:15.475 --> 20:17.955
Are these the two
who were at your dojo?

20:17.999 --> 20:21.132
The ones who killed Gary
and tried to get to you?

20:24.397 --> 20:26.442
Uh, no.

20:26.486 --> 20:28.314
Those aren't them.
Those aren't the guys.

20:29.489 --> 20:30.490
What?

20:30.533 --> 20:32.666
Yeah.

20:32.709 --> 20:34.276
Never seen them before
in my life.

20:34.320 --> 20:39.412
♪♪

20:39.455 --> 20:44.286
♪♪

20:49.335 --> 20:51.946
Hope you got everything
you needed.

20:51.989 --> 20:53.643
Bridger,
what really happened?

20:53.687 --> 20:55.210
Excuse me.

20:55.254 --> 20:56.472
Did the cartel come here
and threaten you?

20:56.516 --> 20:59.475
Uh...

20:59.519 --> 21:03.392
N-No, I -- I was mistaken...
about my last statement.

21:03.436 --> 21:05.481
Um...

21:05.525 --> 21:07.353
It was hard to tell
exactly what happened.

21:07.396 --> 21:08.528
Bridger, I need you
to tell me the truth.

21:08.571 --> 21:10.530
An innocent man
was murdered.

21:10.573 --> 21:13.359
Hey, we're done here.
You have his statement.

21:13.402 --> 21:14.795
He didn't see anything.

21:14.838 --> 21:16.536
No one here is on trial.

21:16.579 --> 21:17.798
We gave you our statements.

21:17.841 --> 21:20.453
Honey,
go to your room.

21:23.847 --> 21:24.805
Chuck: After you.

21:29.549 --> 21:31.333
You going somewhere?

21:31.377 --> 21:33.553
Thanks so much
for stopping by.

21:33.596 --> 21:36.556
Look, Bridger,
we can protect you.

21:36.599 --> 21:37.948
You just have to
trust us.

21:37.992 --> 21:39.210
You have our numbers.

21:39.254 --> 21:41.212
Call me directly
from here on out.

21:44.259 --> 21:46.261
[ Telephone ringing ]

21:50.483 --> 21:51.701
They got to the family,

21:51.745 --> 21:53.703
made Bridger change
his statement.

21:53.747 --> 21:55.401
Can we prove that?

21:55.444 --> 21:58.099
Of course not.
Damn it, we needed that witness!

21:59.666 --> 22:01.407
What about T-Lock?
Anything?

22:01.450 --> 22:02.669
Not yet.

22:04.584 --> 22:06.542
How about
your friend Travis?

22:06.586 --> 22:08.762
What about him?

22:08.805 --> 22:10.416
Maybe he could help.

22:12.026 --> 22:14.855
You know he's undercover.

22:14.898 --> 22:16.509
I don't want to put him
in any more risk.

22:16.552 --> 22:18.598
Jenny, right now,
we got nothing.

22:18.641 --> 22:20.600
I'd say it's worth that risk.

22:20.643 --> 22:23.994
♪♪

22:24.038 --> 22:25.996
Call you later.

22:26.040 --> 22:27.389
[ Sighs ][ Door closes ]

22:27.433 --> 22:32.351
♪♪

22:34.483 --> 22:42.099
♪♪

22:42.143 --> 22:43.231
A "thank you"
would be nice.

22:43.274 --> 22:44.493
[ Door closes ]

22:45.842 --> 22:47.844
What are
you talking about?

22:47.888 --> 22:49.542
I got to that kid Bridger's
parents.

22:49.585 --> 22:53.589
The lawyers fixed it
for you.

22:53.633 --> 22:55.374
Thanks, Ren. You're always
looking out for me.

22:57.376 --> 22:59.421
Okay. We're not doing
some sort of group hug.

22:59.465 --> 23:01.205
What's next?
You gonna tell Dad?

23:01.249 --> 23:02.903
Depends.

23:02.946 --> 23:05.427
You trash my idea
to move operations here?

23:05.471 --> 23:07.908
I won't have to.
It's a bad idea.

23:07.951 --> 23:10.911
Kinda like
shooting up a dojo?

23:10.954 --> 23:13.435
I knew you were unhinged
and lazy,

23:13.479 --> 23:15.002
but straight-up stupid?

23:15.045 --> 23:17.613
Name-calling.
Well, that's productive.

23:17.657 --> 23:20.921
Look,
Dad wanted the money.

23:20.964 --> 23:22.705
We do what Dad wants.

23:22.749 --> 23:25.621
Yeah.
Kinda done with that.

23:25.665 --> 23:26.622
What are you saying?

23:26.666 --> 23:28.058
You'll see.

23:29.495 --> 23:30.844
Ren.

23:30.887 --> 23:32.715
Ren!

23:32.759 --> 23:35.283
What the hell
is that supposed to mean?

23:39.287 --> 23:41.158
What day are
we talking about again?

23:41.202 --> 23:43.334
The day an RV was stolen
from here.

23:43.378 --> 23:44.466
Or does that happen a lot?

23:44.510 --> 23:46.033
You'd be surprised.

23:46.076 --> 23:48.862
[ Mouse clicks ]

23:48.905 --> 23:53.649
♪♪

23:53.693 --> 23:54.824
Whoa. Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

23:54.868 --> 23:55.825
Stop, stop, stop, stop.

23:55.869 --> 23:59.481
[ Mouse clicks ]

23:59.525 --> 24:06.096
♪♪

24:06.140 --> 24:08.534
Whoa. Holy moly,
mother of mackerel.

24:08.577 --> 24:10.753
[ Chuckles ]
We got ya.

24:10.797 --> 24:15.671
♪♪

24:15.715 --> 24:16.890
[ Door opens ]

24:20.328 --> 24:21.982
Where's Ren?

24:22.025 --> 24:23.549
Gone.

24:23.592 --> 24:26.639
You know my sister --
always up to something.

24:26.682 --> 24:27.944
How about you?

24:27.988 --> 24:30.425
Productive day?

24:30.469 --> 24:31.687
You could say so.

24:31.731 --> 24:33.602
You want some Scotch?

24:33.646 --> 24:34.951
It's a 12-year-old
single malt.

24:34.995 --> 24:36.692
No, thank you.

24:36.736 --> 24:38.694
I actually don't drink.

24:38.738 --> 24:40.217
I'm five years sober.

24:40.261 --> 24:42.742
Mm. I admire that.

24:42.785 --> 24:45.745
Especially since we're gonna be
in business together.

24:45.788 --> 24:47.398
My sister thinks highly
of you,

24:47.442 --> 24:49.705
and I can see why.

24:49.749 --> 24:51.794
[ Chuckles ]

24:51.838 --> 24:54.449
She's told me
so much about you.

24:54.493 --> 24:57.017
[ Chuckles ]
I can only imagine.

24:57.060 --> 25:01.543
Um, handsome, charming,
et cetera?

25:01.587 --> 25:03.893
I'm kidding.

25:03.937 --> 25:06.200
I know exactly
what my sister thinks of me.

25:07.636 --> 25:09.029
Brothers and sisters.

25:09.072 --> 25:10.465
It's complicated, you know.

25:10.509 --> 25:13.381
Yeah.

25:13.424 --> 25:15.775
I have a sister who's difficult.

25:15.818 --> 25:18.255
See? You get it.

25:18.299 --> 25:20.431
Ren also told me
about the ranch --

25:20.475 --> 25:23.217
how you not only found it
but even helped her close it.

25:23.260 --> 25:24.827
That's right.

25:24.871 --> 25:26.394
That is impressive.

25:26.437 --> 25:28.048
Especially in this market.

25:28.091 --> 25:30.659
You must be some sort of
real-estate whiz.

25:30.703 --> 25:34.663
I wouldn't say that,
but it helps to have a local.

25:35.621 --> 25:37.579
But why a ranch?

25:37.623 --> 25:39.799
She has her plans.

25:39.842 --> 25:42.584
I think. Or a plan.

25:45.456 --> 25:48.459
I think you should
talk to her about it.

25:49.852 --> 25:52.681
Loyalty.

25:52.725 --> 25:54.204
I admire that.

25:56.206 --> 25:58.818
But here's the thing,
Tonya.

25:58.861 --> 26:00.820
We are on the same team.

26:00.863 --> 26:04.388
And I can only help
if you open up to me, Tonya.

26:04.432 --> 26:06.869
So why don't you walk me
through the plan?

26:06.913 --> 26:15.486
♪♪

26:15.530 --> 26:16.792
[ Gun clatters ]

26:18.141 --> 26:19.795
Mom?

26:23.016 --> 26:25.018
[ Sighs ]

26:31.372 --> 26:34.810
This car belonged to Wolf.
Right?

26:34.854 --> 26:37.900
And Wolf was a mean,
mean man.

26:37.944 --> 26:40.424
And this was his.

26:40.468 --> 26:43.123
We're not mean like Wolf,
are we, Phoebe?

26:45.734 --> 26:46.692
That's right.

26:52.915 --> 26:54.351
[ Sighs ] Okay.

26:56.702 --> 27:00.575
♪♪

27:00.619 --> 27:02.708
[ Seatbelt rattles ]

27:02.751 --> 27:04.448
Stay in the car.

27:04.492 --> 27:06.320
What's the matter?

27:06.363 --> 27:09.671
Just stay in the car
for a minute, okay?

27:09.715 --> 27:17.026
♪♪

27:17.070 --> 27:24.686
♪♪

27:24.730 --> 27:32.476
♪♪

27:32.520 --> 27:34.217
[ Gasps ]

27:39.353 --> 27:43.923
♪♪

27:43.966 --> 27:47.753
Okay, Sweetie. So, there's been
a change of plans.

27:47.796 --> 27:49.493
We're not gonna stay here,
because this place,

27:49.537 --> 27:52.366
it doesn't have a pool,
it doesn't have pancakes

27:52.409 --> 27:53.933
or french toast
for breakfast, so --

27:53.976 --> 27:56.631
[ Ronald coughs,
groans weakly ]

27:56.675 --> 27:59.068
Okay. Um, I'm gonna need you
to be a good girl,

27:59.112 --> 28:00.722
and I need you
to sit down, okay?

28:00.766 --> 28:03.594
Just --
Just relax a minute.

28:04.770 --> 28:06.772
Hi.

28:06.815 --> 28:08.774
[ Breathes shakily ] Okay.

28:10.819 --> 28:13.953
Phoebe: Mom?What -- What is it, honey?

28:13.996 --> 28:17.086
[ Breathing heavily ]

28:17.130 --> 28:18.914
[ Ronald groans weakly ]

28:23.049 --> 28:25.616
Okay, Ronald...

28:25.660 --> 28:27.923
Ronald,
I need you to get up.

28:27.967 --> 28:29.533
I need you to get up,
okay?

28:29.577 --> 28:31.797
I need you to get up.

28:31.840 --> 28:33.755
Okay.
Okay, baby, wait.

28:33.799 --> 28:35.888
Oh, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no. You're okay.

28:35.931 --> 28:37.803
We got to get up.Okay.

28:37.846 --> 28:39.979
Okay.

28:40.022 --> 28:41.110
[ Grunts ]

28:41.154 --> 28:42.808
Honey,
grab your backpack.

28:42.851 --> 28:43.765
Come on, quick.

28:43.809 --> 28:45.549
Open the door.

28:45.593 --> 28:52.948
♪♪

28:52.992 --> 28:55.559
[ Chuckles ] What?

28:55.603 --> 28:56.909
You look like hell.

28:56.952 --> 28:58.867
Yeah, well,
back-to-back all-nighters.

29:01.043 --> 29:02.653
I remember those.Mm.

29:02.697 --> 29:03.785
Cheers.

29:05.831 --> 29:07.746
[ Bottle cap clatters ]

29:10.009 --> 29:11.619
Did you hear anything
about Bridger Ryan?

29:11.662 --> 29:12.968
[ Chuckles ]

29:13.012 --> 29:14.143
[ Bottle cap clatters ]

29:14.187 --> 29:15.405
Right into business.

29:15.449 --> 29:17.277
Okay.

29:17.320 --> 29:20.584
The Bhullars got to him
and his family.

29:20.628 --> 29:22.848
He recanted.
I had to let Jag go.

29:23.979 --> 29:25.807
That's what they do.

29:25.851 --> 29:28.070
They wouldn't go after
his family, would they?

29:28.114 --> 29:30.464
They will
if they have to, yeah.

29:30.507 --> 29:33.032
But let's hope it doesn't
come to that, right?

29:33.075 --> 29:34.685
[ Sighs ]

29:34.729 --> 29:36.731
I got nothing on Jag Bhullar
without Bridger's statement.

29:39.125 --> 29:41.605
That money ever turn up?

29:41.649 --> 29:43.869
[ Sighs ] No.

29:43.912 --> 29:45.348
Where are you at with it?

29:46.872 --> 29:48.525
A guy named T-Lock has it.

29:48.569 --> 29:51.093
A local lowlife who's dating
one of the kids' moms.

29:57.534 --> 29:58.622
You know him?

29:58.666 --> 30:00.581
Nope.

30:02.235 --> 30:03.062
Why?

30:05.978 --> 30:07.457
Just wondering.

30:07.501 --> 30:09.851
Uh, can we -- can we, um --
I'm sorry.

30:09.895 --> 30:11.853
Can we talk about something
other than work?

30:14.116 --> 30:15.683
Please.

30:15.726 --> 30:16.771
Please.

30:19.165 --> 30:20.862
I have an idea.

30:20.906 --> 30:22.429
Oh, yeah?
Mm-hmm.

30:22.472 --> 30:23.604
I have an idea, too.

30:25.606 --> 30:26.868
[ Chuckles ]

30:26.912 --> 30:28.696
You're coming with me.

30:28.739 --> 30:30.089
Oh, yeah?
W-What is this?!

30:30.132 --> 30:31.917
[ Both laugh ]

30:31.960 --> 30:35.921
[ Jet engine roaring ]

30:40.360 --> 30:41.927
What?

30:41.970 --> 30:43.363
Did you tell Ren
about this?

30:43.406 --> 30:44.364
Nope.

30:44.407 --> 30:45.887
You sure?

30:45.931 --> 30:48.672
I know when to keep
my mouth shut.

30:48.716 --> 30:49.891
All right. Well...

30:49.935 --> 30:51.458
Go ahead.

30:51.501 --> 30:53.939
I know you have thoughts.

30:53.982 --> 30:56.245
She's not gonna like
you going behind her back.

30:56.289 --> 30:59.379
Maybe. Then again,
I don't really care.

30:59.422 --> 31:01.947
[ Chuckles ]

31:02.382 --> 31:03.949
What is it with you two,
anyway?

31:08.867 --> 31:10.912
She would
eat you alive, bro.

31:10.956 --> 31:12.044
Don't even go there.

31:12.087 --> 31:13.828
I respect her.

31:13.872 --> 31:15.917
She's got...skills.

31:15.961 --> 31:19.094
Yeah, okay.

31:19.138 --> 31:22.097
Well, next time you're simping,
ask her about Billy.

31:22.141 --> 31:23.925
Old boyfriend.

31:23.969 --> 31:25.535
Dead boyfriend.

31:32.586 --> 31:34.109
[ Clears throat ]

31:36.155 --> 31:36.895
Ah!

31:39.158 --> 31:41.725
Get out of my shot.

31:41.769 --> 31:43.031
[ Clears throat ]

31:43.075 --> 31:45.294
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

31:45.338 --> 31:46.948
[ Laughs ]

31:46.992 --> 31:49.733
Okay, come on,
darling!

31:49.777 --> 32:01.789
♪♪

32:01.832 --> 32:03.704
[ Sighs ]

32:06.228 --> 32:08.056
Sat siri Akaal,
uncle Ji.

32:11.190 --> 32:14.236
[ Sighs ]
Welcome to Montana, Dad.

32:14.280 --> 32:19.024
♪♪

32:19.067 --> 32:20.025
Dietrich: [ Whistles ]

32:20.068 --> 32:22.244
Lucky you showed.

32:22.288 --> 32:25.073
Oh, yeah?
And why's that?

32:25.117 --> 32:27.423
Well, Bob lost our bet.

32:27.467 --> 32:30.470
He was having doubts
about our deal.

32:30.513 --> 32:31.819
Said you wouldn't be back.

32:31.862 --> 32:34.256
Really?

32:34.300 --> 32:37.216
Well, here I am.

32:37.259 --> 32:38.608
What'd you lose?

32:38.652 --> 32:42.134
Chance to turn your piggy ass
into kielbasa.

32:42.177 --> 32:44.049
[ Laughs ]
Careful now, Bobby boy.

32:44.092 --> 32:46.138
See, you're getting
all jittery.

32:46.181 --> 32:47.704
You don't want to do that when
you're this close to the prize.

32:47.748 --> 32:50.490
Yeah, about that.

32:50.533 --> 32:52.231
Taking down the Bhullars.

32:52.274 --> 32:55.016
I want the old man --
Veer Bhullar.

32:55.060 --> 32:57.497
Sounds personal.

32:57.540 --> 32:59.499
Maybe.

32:59.542 --> 33:01.240
Well, how 'bout you tell me
where my money is first

33:01.283 --> 33:03.677
before we go tilting after
Veer Bhullar?

33:03.720 --> 33:07.681
5.56 77 grain
full metal jacket.

33:07.724 --> 33:11.467
I am good
up to 600 yards.

33:11.511 --> 33:14.209
No need to get our hands dirty
if you let me do what I do.

33:14.253 --> 33:15.689
Yeah, this is
not a gopher shoot, but --

33:15.732 --> 33:17.082
Oh, I see -- you like it
up close and personal, huh?

33:17.125 --> 33:19.127
Okay, we're getting
sidetracked.

33:22.478 --> 33:23.653
My money?

33:23.697 --> 33:26.221
T-Lock has it.

33:26.265 --> 33:28.702
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, that's funny.Yeah?

33:28.745 --> 33:30.312
Yeah, considering
that was the guy

33:30.356 --> 33:32.140
you were supposed to kill.

33:32.184 --> 33:33.446
It's ironic.

33:33.489 --> 33:34.969
Mm.

33:35.013 --> 33:36.275
Don't suppose you know
where he is.

33:36.318 --> 33:39.321
No. I'm gonna let you
figure that out, D.

33:39.365 --> 33:44.413
♪♪

33:44.457 --> 33:46.894
I, uh, can't wait to
show you both around.

33:46.937 --> 33:48.287
It's a really lovely time
of year.

33:48.330 --> 33:52.421
Ah, gorgeous.
The mountains?

33:52.465 --> 33:56.469
You know, I really want to see
a buffalo or bison.

33:56.512 --> 33:57.687
Do you say both?

33:57.731 --> 34:01.256
Bison. Better.

34:01.300 --> 34:03.911
Puttar,I'm not
a tourist here.

34:03.954 --> 34:05.565
You called.

